# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Model Families
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Tree-Based Models is a ModelFamily
Linear Models is a ModelFamily
Neural Network Models is a ModelFamily
SVM Models is a ModelFamily
Nearest Neighbor Models is a ModelFamily
Naive Bayes Models is a ModelFamily

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Operator → Family membership
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Tree-Based
sklearn.ensemble.RandomForestClassifier belongs to family Tree-Based Models
sklearn.ensemble.GradientBoostingClassifier belongs to family Tree-Based Models
sklearn.ensemble.HistGradientBoostingClassifier belongs to family Tree-Based Models
sklearn.ensemble.AdaBoostClassifier belongs to family Tree-Based Models
sklearn.ensemble.ExtraTreesClassifier belongs to family Tree-Based Models
sklearn.tree.DecisionTreeClassifier belongs to family Tree-Based Models

# Linear
sklearn.linear_model.LogisticRegression belongs to family Linear Models
sklearn.linear_model.SGDClassifier belongs to family Linear Models
sklearn.linear_model.PassiveAggressiveClassifier belongs to family Linear Models
sklearn.discriminant_analysis.LinearDiscriminantAnalysis belongs to family Linear Models

# SVM
sklearn.svm.SVC belongs to family SVM Models
sklearn.svm.LinearSVC belongs to family SVM Models

# Nearest Neighbor
sklearn.neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier belongs to family Nearest Neighbor Models

# Naive Bayes
sklearn.naive_bayes.GaussianNB belongs to family Naive Bayes Models
sklearn.naive_bayes.BernoulliNB belongs to family Naive Bayes Models
sklearn.naive_bayes.MultinomialNB belongs to family Naive Bayes Models

# Neural Network
sklearn.neural_network.MLPClassifier belongs to family Neural Network Models

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DQ Metric → Risk surface
# "when this metric fails its threshold, this risk is surfaced"
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

ValueCompleteness surfaces risk Missing Value Bias
RecordCompleteness surfaces risk Missing Value Bias
LabelCompleteness surfaces risk Label Noise
LabelDistributionBalance surfaces risk Class Imbalance
LabelProportionBalance surfaces risk Class Imbalance
DataRecordConsistency surfaces risk Data Leakage
SyntacticDataAccuracy surfaces risk Measurement Bias
SemanticDataAccuracy surfaces risk Measurement Bias
SampleIndependency surfaces risk Covariate Shift
SampleTightness surfaces risk Distribution Shift
CategorySizeDiversity surfaces risk Aggregation Bias
DataFormatConsistency surfaces risk Measurement Bias
FeatureRelevance surfaces risk Proxy Features
RiskOfDatasetInaccuracy surfaces risk Outlier Bias

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Risk → Sensitive model families
# "this risk hurts these model families more than others"
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Missing Value Bias sensitive family Linear Models
Missing Value Bias sensitive family SVM Models
Missing Value Bias sensitive family Nearest Neighbor Models
Class Imbalance sensitive family Linear Models
Class Imbalance sensitive family Nearest Neighbor Models
Covariate Shift sensitive family Linear Models
Covariate Shift sensitive family Naive Bayes Models
Distribution Shift sensitive family Neural Network Models
Distribution Shift sensitive family SVM Models
Outlier Bias sensitive family Linear Models
Outlier Bias sensitive family Nearest Neighbor Models
Outlier Bias sensitive family SVM Models

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Cross-View Pathway Rules
#
# Each pathway links a DQ metric condition to pipeline-aware actions.
# At runtime, evaluate_pathways() queries these nodes, checks current
# metric values against thresholds, filters by pipeline operator
# families, and emits matching pathways as AI Debugger suggestions.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Pathway 1: High missingness + NaN-intolerant models ──
missingness_sensitivity is a Pathway
missingness_sensitivity when below ValueCompleteness; has threshold 0.90
missingness_sensitivity and contains family Linear Models
missingness_sensitivity and contains family SVM Models
missingness_sensitivity and contains family Nearest Neighbor Models
missingness_sensitivity suggests preprocessing sklearn.impute.SimpleImputer
missingness_sensitivity suggests replacement Tree-Based Models
missingness_sensitivity with description "ValueCompleteness is {metric_value} — {family} cannot handle missing values. Add SimpleImputer before {operator}, or switch to HistGradientBoosting which handles NaN natively."

# ── Pathway 2: Class imbalance + any classifier ──
imbalance_classifier is a Pathway
imbalance_classifier when above LabelDistributionBalance; has threshold 0.15
imbalance_classifier and performs task Classification
imbalance_classifier suggests preprocessing imblearn.over_sampling.SMOTE
imbalance_classifier with description "Label distribution divergence is {metric_value}. Add SMOTE before {operator} to balance classes, or set class_weight='balanced'."

# ── Pathway 3: Duplication → data leakage ──
duplication_leakage is a Pathway
duplication_leakage when above DataRecordConsistency; has threshold 0.05
duplication_leakage with description "Dataset has {metric_value_pct}% duplicate records. Remove duplicates before training to prevent data leakage across train/test splits."

# ── Pathway 4: Low feature independence + linear models ──
multicollinearity_linear is a Pathway
multicollinearity_linear when below SampleIndependency; has threshold 0.70
multicollinearity_linear and contains family Linear Models
multicollinearity_linear suggests preprocessing sklearn.decomposition.PCA
multicollinearity_linear suggests replacement Tree-Based Models
multicollinearity_linear with description "Features are highly correlated (independency={metric_value}). Add PCA to decorrelate, or switch to tree-based models which handle multicollinearity."

# ── Pathway 5: Low syntactic accuracy + any model ──
syntactic_noise is a Pathway
syntactic_noise when below SyntacticDataAccuracy; has threshold 0.85
syntactic_noise with description "Syntactic accuracy is {metric_value}. Run syntactic repair (exact match → fuzzy matching → LLM judgment) to fix invalid values before training."

# ── Pathway 6: Tight samples + neural networks ──
tight_samples_neural is a Pathway
tight_samples_neural when below SampleTightness; has threshold 0.05
tight_samples_neural and contains family Neural Network Models
tight_samples_neural suggests preprocessing sklearn.preprocessing.StandardScaler
tight_samples_neural with description "Dataset has very tight clustering (tightness={metric_value}). Neural networks need variance for gradient flow — add StandardScaler."

# ── Pathway 7: Outlier risk + sensitive models ──
outlier_sensitivity is a Pathway
outlier_sensitivity when above RiskOfDatasetInaccuracy; has threshold 0.10
outlier_sensitivity and contains family Linear Models
outlier_sensitivity and contains family Nearest Neighbor Models
outlier_sensitivity and contains family SVM Models
outlier_sensitivity suggests preprocessing sklearn.preprocessing.RobustScaler
outlier_sensitivity with description "Dataset has {metric_value_pct}% outlier risk. {family} is sensitive to outliers — add RobustScaler or apply Winsorization."

# ── Pathway 8: Low label completeness + supervised learning ──
label_gap is a Pathway
label_gap when below LabelCompleteness; has threshold 0.85
label_gap and performs task Classification
label_gap with description "Label completeness is {metric_value}. Remove unlabeled records or consider semi-supervised learning approaches."
